  "full_prompt": "Design the 1U CubeSat primary structural bus for an African-regional student CubeSat benchmark, launching via a standard P-POD-compliant dispenser, as a multi-part bolted assembly. The assembly consists of four corner deployer rails, four body side panels (\u00b1X, \u00b1Y), a top payload aperture panel, a bottom deployer-interface panel, a central payload tray with four M3 mounting bosses on an 80 x 80 mm bolt pattern, and the fastener / hardware set. Envelope must comply with CDS Rev 14.1: 100.0 mm +/- 0.1 mm x 100.0 mm +/- 0.1 mm x 113.5 mm +/- 0.1 mm maximum, with four deployer rails of 8.5 mm minimum width at each corner, a minimum 75% anodized rail surface, and center of mass within +/- 2 cm of geometric center on each axis. Total wet mass must not exceed 2.0 kg. Material: Aluminum 6061-T6 (Young's modulus 68.9 GPa, Poisson 0.33, yield 276 MPa, ultimate 310 MPa, density 2700 kg/m^3). Payload slot must expose a top aperture of at least 60 x 60 mm for a camera sensor and supply four M3 mounting bosses on an 80 x 80 mm bolt pattern. Load cases: (LC1) quasi-static launch: 14 g applied simultaneously on each of the three body axes on the wet 2.0 kg mass; (LC2) random vibration per CDS 14.1 Grms qualification profile (20-2000 Hz ASD table), response captured over 2 minutes per axis; (LC3) sine sweep: 10-100 Hz at 2 g base sweep, one octave per minute; (LC4) thermal cycling: -40 C to +85 C, 10 cycles, as a uniform swing with a 15 C internal electronics delta. Pass/fail per NASA-STD-5001B protoflight: max von Mises <= 276 / 1.25 = 220 MPa on yield and 310 / 1.4 = 221 MPa on ultimate under LC1; first natural frequency >= 100 Hz; random-vib 3-sigma response stress <= 220 MPa; thermal-deformation-induced CM shift <= 2 mm on any axis. Verification is performed on the assembled bolted model with representative M3 fastener stiffness at every panel/rail interface; per-part stress is reported but does not gate pass/fail. Deliverables: STEP with all bodies, modal (first 10 modes), FEA per case on assembly, random-vib PSD response report, thermal displacement contour, and mass/CM report.",
  "short_prompt": "Design the 1U CubeSat primary structural bus for an African-regional student CubeSat benchmark, launching via a P-POD-compliant dispenser, as a multi-part bolted assembly.\n\nEnvelope per CDS Rev 14.1: 100.0 +/- 0.1 mm x 100.0 +/- 0.1 mm x 113.5 +/- 0.1 mm maximum, four deployer rails of 8.5 mm minimum width at each corner, >= 75% anodized, CM within +/- 2 cm. Wet mass <= 2.0 kg. Material Aluminum 6061-T6 (E 68.9 GPa, Poisson 0.33, yield 276 MPa, ultimate 310 MPa, density 2700 kg/m^3). Qualification per NASA-STD-5001B protoflight (yield FoS 1.25, ultimate FoS 1.4).\n\nLoad cases.\n- LC1 quasi-static launch: 14 g simultaneous on each of three body axes on wet 2.0 kg.\n- LC2 random vibration per CDS 14.1 Grms, 20-2000 Hz, 2 minutes per axis.\n- LC3 sine sweep: 10-100 Hz at 2 g base sweep, one octave per minute.\n- LC4 thermal cycling: -40 C to +85 C, 10 cycles, with 15 C internal electronics delta.\n\nFirst mode >= 100 Hz; thermal-induced CM shift <= 2 mm on any axis.",
